title: Microsoft CEO to employees: No longer enough to be software factory, must become…

author: SOUMITRA BOSE
description: Following a tragic road accident on the Nagpur-Madhya Pradesh highway, a man was compelled to transport his wife's body home on his motorcycle due to the absence of immediate assistance. The incident occurred near Deolapar, where an unidentified vehicle struck their motorcycle, resulting in the woman's death.
title: Nagpur: Man rides 80km with wife’s body tied to bike after fatal highway crash

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: China has officially launched the Xinjiang Tibet Railway Co. Ltd., initiating work on the strategic railway line near India's Ladakh border. This project, involving significant investment and traversing challenging terrain, aims to enhance connectivity between Xinjiang and Tibet.
title: Along Ladakh border, China to construct Xinjiang-Tibet rail line

author: APEKSHA TANWAR
description: With less than two weeks before the US fall semester, Indian students face a severe F-1 visa crisis marked by appointment shortages and rising rejections. Student arrivals may drop nearly 70%, disrupting academic plans and US university revenues. Delays stem from stricter screening, suspended interviews, and regulatory changes, pushing many to consider alternative study destinations.
title: F-1 visa chaos: Why Indian student approvals are plummeting before US fall se

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Supreme Court upheld Medha Patkar's conviction in a defamation case initiated by VK Saxena. However, the court removed the Rs 1 lakh penalty previously imposed. A Delhi court had earlier issued a warrant against Patkar for not complying with the sentencing order. The Delhi High Court had also supported Patkar's conviction, stating that her challenge relied on minor technicalities.
title: Medha Patkar case: SC upholds activist's conviction in VK Saxena's defamation case

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Supreme Court addressed dog bite incidents in Delhi. It directed the Delhi government to remove stray dogs from all areas. The dogs will be kept in shelters and not released back. Shelters with staff for sterilization and immunization must be created. A helpline will be set up within a week for reporting dog bites.
title: 'Situation grim': SC directs Delhi govt, MCD to start picking up stray dogs

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Nitin Gadkari indirectly criticised US President Donald Trump's tariff policies, asserting that financial strength and technological advancement shouldn't lead to bullying. He emphasised India's commitment to its culture of global welfare, even with economic growth. Gadkari also highlighted the importance of innovation and research to boost India's economic growth and self-reliance.
title: ‘They are financially strong ...’: Gadkari’s veiled ‘dadagiri’ jibe amid Trump tariffs

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Aakash Chopra suggested that both Australia and South Africa, the finalists of the previous WTC cycle, might face difficulties in reaching the 2027 final. Despite Australia's strong start, their tour of India and an aging bowling attack could hinder their progress. South Africa's challenging away series in the subcontinent also diminish their chances of qualifying, according to Chopra.
title: 'They will lose to India’: Ex-cricketer doubts Aus & SA’s WTC final chances

author: TNN
description: Moshik Shanmugasundaram, a 21-year-old college student, was fatally stabbed at a Puducherry restobar following a late-night birthday celebration with friends. An argument with the restobar owner and staff over closing time escalated into a brawl.
title: 'Came to celebrate birthday': Knife attack at Puducherry bar leaves 1 student dead

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is offering 800 permanent memberships to the prestigious Siri Fort Sports Complex (SFSC). Applications are open online from August 12 to September 11, 2025, for government employees, non-government individuals, and existing members. Selection will be through a lottery or based on membership history, providing access to world-class sports amenities.
title: DDA Siri fort 2025 membership: Apply online from Aug 12 – Details here

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Al Jazeera correspondent Anas al-Sharif was killed in an Israeli airstrike in Gaza, along with four other journalists. Prior to his death, al-Sharif posted a video documenting the intense bombardment of Gaza City, leaving behind a final message reflecting on his life and commitment to conveying the truth.
title: ‘If these words reach you ...’: Al Jazeera reporter’s ‘final message’ before being killed

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Before their divorce, Bill and Melinda Gates navigated parenting challenges. Bill's insistence on driving their daughter Jennifer to a distant kindergarten, despite his demanding role as Microsoft CEO, surprised Melinda. This decision not only created cherished moments for Bill and his daughter but also inspired other fathers in their community to become more involved in school drop-offs, reshaping family dynamics.
title: Melinda on Bill Gates driving daughter to school: Moms said class ‘changed’

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated 184 new flats for Members of Parliament in New Delhi, emphasizing modern amenities and green technology. The complex, designed for self-sufficiency and sustainability, incorporates features like renewable power generation and improved waste management.
title: PM Modi’s ‘Kosi’ jibe at opposition at MP flats launch in Delhi

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: David Justice reflected on his marriage with Halle Berry, citing youth, distance, and traditional expectations as contributing factors to their divorce. He expressed regret over not seeking counseling, believing it could have helped them navigate their challenges. Justice's remarks about Berry's domestic skills sparked online debate, highlighting evolving views on gender roles in marriage.
title: ‘Probably could’ve made it’: David Justice reflects on Halle Berry split

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Election Commission has pressed Rahul Gandhi to substantiate his claims of "vote theft" in Karnataka and Haryana, demanding either a formal declaration supporting his allegations or a public apology. The Karnataka CEO has requested documents related to Gandhi's assertion that a voter cast two ballots, citing discrepancies in ECI records.

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former selector Devang Gandhi feels India’s next-gen stars are ready for all formats, raising doubts over Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli’s ODI futures. He urged selectors to plan early, noting Shubman Gill’s captaincy credentials. Gandhi stressed both veterans may need domestic one-day stints to prolong careers, though their willingness to endure the grind remains uncertain.

author: ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Rajinikanth's 'Coolie', directed by Lokesh Kanagaraj, is creating a box office frenzy ahead of its release. Worldwide advance bookings have surpassed Rs 50 crore, with strong overseas sales, particularly in North America where it exceeded 'Leo's premiere record. Domestically, pre-sales have overtaken 'Jailer', potentially marking Rajinikanth's biggest opening ever and a historic moment for Indian cinema.

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold price prediction today: Gold prices are projected to remain range-bound amid global economic uncertainties. Last week, prices hit record highs domestically due to rate cut expectations and a weak US jobs report. A false tariff report briefly spiked prices before a correction. Market focus now shifts to key US inflation and retail sales data.

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Air India refuted Congress MP KC Venugopal's account of a harrowing flight, stating the diversion to Chennai was due to a suspected technical issue and poor weather, not another aircraft on the runway. Venugopal dismissed Air India's explanation, demanding an inquiry and alleging the airline was lying. BJP's Amit Malviya called the matter serious, highlighting the contradiction and demanding accountability.

description: Akash Deep reflected on India's drawn series in England, highlighting his experiences and interactions, including a verbal exchange with Ben Duckett. He valued his half-century more than a ten-wicket haul and dedicated his performance to his sister battling cancer. Akash Deep also praised Mohammed Siraj's fitness and mental fortitude during the series.

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Short-track racing lost a star as Robbie Brewer, 53, tragically passed away after a heart attack during a race at Bowman Gray Stadium. On August 9, Brewer's car crashed in turn 4, leading to fatal injuries. A fixture at Bowman Gray for over 35 years, Brewer's accomplishments included 11 Sportsman wins and the 2011 championship.

author: GAURAV GUPTA
description: Former India captain Dilip Vengsarkar believed Jasprit Bumrah should have skipped IPL 2025 to stay fresh for the England Test series. He also suggested that Virat Kohli should have played the series before retiring. Vengsarkar emphasised the importance of Test cricket, highlighting standout performances from Siraj, Gill, Rahul, Jaiswal, Pant and Sundar. He defended Bumrah's workload management, citing his back surgery.

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Kourtney Kardashian Barker faced online criticism after posting boat photos where her son, Rocky Thirteen, wasn't wearing a life jacket. Followers raised safety concerns, prompting Kourtney to purchase a life vest and acknowledge the oversight. This incident highlights a common issue: parents sometimes skip life jackets for reasons like short trips or discomfort.
title: Fans call out Kourtney Kardashian over son’s safety on boat

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: Astronomers have spotted a giant planet, TOI-6894b, orbiting a tiny red dwarf star, challenging existing planet formation theories. This gas giant, larger than Saturn but less massive, orbits a star only one-fifth the Sun's mass. The discovery suggests that large planets might be more common around small stars than previously believed.

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A disturbing video from Sweida, Syria, shows armed men, allegedly Syrian military and security personnel, fatally shooting a medical worker at a hospital. The incident occurred during clashes between Druze militias, tribal groups, and government forces. Syrian authorities have launched an investigation to identify the perpetrators, vowing to bring them to justice regardless of affiliation, while activists claim the attackers were government forces.

author: TOI Education
description: The Institute of Cost Accountants of India (ICMAI) has released the CMA June 2025 Intermediate and Final results on its official website, icmai.in. Pass percentages varied across groups, reflecting mixed trends compared to December 2024, with some declines in key categories.

description: The Institute of Cost Accountants of India (ICMAI) has announced the CMA June 2025 Intermediate and Final exam toppers, with Hans Amresh from Surat securing the first rank. The top 10 list features candidates from cities including Mumbai, Jaipur, Faridabad, and Bangalore, reflecting wide geographic representation and notable female participation in this year’s merit rankings.

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK

Delhi Police stated that no permission was sought for the protest. The opposition raised concerns about fake forms and discrepancies in voter lists, demanding electronic data for verification.
